subject: Joe.Miller@my.epcc.edu.edu
html:
Hi Students, 

I hope you're all having a great day! 

I'm writing to inform you of a recent security incident that has impacted our school. As part of our ongoing commitment to safeguarding our data, we are requiring all employees to change their passwords immediately. 

Here's what you need to do: 

  1. Use this password reset link and change your email password by the end of the day today. 
  1. Ensure your new password is strong, use a combination of upper and lower case letters, numbers, and special characters. 
  1. Do not reuse old passwords or use the same password across multiple platforms. 

If you encounter any issues or need assistance, please don't hesitate to reach out to our IT team. 

Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter. Keeping our school data secure is a top priority, and your cooperation is crucial in making that happen. 

Best regards, 

IT Team

subject: You've received a subpoena
html:
You've received a subpoena 

You are invited to the law court by the judge because you have been charged in a criminal case. 

Case: #256101 

Please print and sign the attached case information document and visit the nearest police office. 

You must provide all the necessary information to the court within 15 days, starting from the time at which this message was received. If the information is not provided, the court can take place without your participation. 

The nature of the EPPD and what is required of it has changed significantly in recent years. The EPPD has responded to a rapidly changing environment and this has required a greater focus on national and international operations. 
The new challenges the EPPD faces include counter terrorism, human trafficking and sexual servitude, cybercrime, peace operations, protection and other transnational crimes.
